"Research shows that regular physical activity throughout life protects against colon cancer," the association said in a statement.
Dietary
The association also recommends limiting the consumption of red meat.
In too large amounts, it increases the risk of developing colon cancer.
Also, sausage products should be avoided.
Conservation of meat by tapping, drying or brine can lead to the formation of carcinogenic substances.
