At the moment, however, the results of these studies cannot be called unambiguous.
According to the SCC, studies of vitamin E give contradictory results.
If one of them showed a decrease in the risk of developing prostate cancer, the other gave the opposite result.
In assessing the effect on the development of vitamin D cancer, there is also no complete clarity.
