The idea worked.
The shelves are set up.
“There’s nothing worse than a half-empty library,” says architect Vinnie Maas.
“I think that thanks to our invitation, every resident is now somehow connected to this new home.
Everyone knows that his book is part of this building.
Even if it's just for decoration.
Thus, MVRDV managed to solve the royal task, which on the professional jargon is called creating identity.
Speikenisse wrote his own literary history.
